<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=347&amp;p=2385#p2385</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=347&amp;p=2385#p2385"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[spr piexel priority]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=347&amp;p=2385#p2385"><![CDATA[
Color 0 is transparent for both BG and sprites.<br /><br />The idea is simple:<br /><br />If both sprite and BG pixels are transparent, output background color (ppu$3F00 when rendering is enabled).  Otherwise:<br /><br />If Sprite is in foreground:<br />-  if sprite pixel is transparent (0), output BG pixel<br />-  else, output sprite pixel<br /><br />Else -- sprite is in backgroud:<br />-  if BG pixel is transparent, output sprite pixel<br />-  else, output BG pixel<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Wed Jun 08, 2005 5:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
